{{wikipedia}}
==English==
[[Image:Lion waiting in Nambia.jpg|thumb|right|250px|A lion.]]

===Etymology===
From {{F.}} ''[[#French|lion]]'', from {{L.}} ''[[leo#Latin|leo]]'', (''genitive: [[leonis]])''. See talk page.

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|/lī'ən/}}, {{IPA|/ˈlaɪən/}}, {{SAMPA|/"laI@n/}}
*{{audio|en-us-lion.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:[[Rhymes:English:-aɪən|Rhymes: -aɪən]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|pl2=lion}}
{{wikispeciespar|Panthera leo}}

# A large [[cat]], ''Panthera leo'', [[native]] to [[Africa]], [[India]] and [[formerly]] to much of [[Europe]].  The term may apply to the [[species]] as a whole, to [[individual]]s, or to [[male]] individuals.  It also applies to related species like [[mountain lion]]s.
# {{heraldiccharge}}: A [[stylized]] [[representation]] of a large cat, used on a [[coat of arms]].
#* The [[arms]] of the University of the West Indies are ''Barry wavy of six Argent and Azure an open Book proper bound Gules garnished Or on a Chief of the third a '''Lion passant guardant Erminois'''. Crest: A Pelican proper''. (in other words a spotted lion lying down). See talk page.
# A [[Chinese]] [[foo dog]].
# {{idiomatic}} An individual who shows [[strength]] and [[courage]], attributes associated with the lion.
# A famous person.

